<%- title "About Sam." -%>

<header>
  <h2><%= link_to 'About Sam.', about_url %></h2>
</header>

<section class="about">
  <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/samsoffes/7148907379/in/set-72157627008591241/lightbox/" rel="external nofollow" id="portrait"><img src="http://assets.samsoff.es/images/Sam-Soffes.jpg" alt="Sam Soffes" /></a>
  <p>I am a <%= link_to 'iOS and Rails software engineer', github_url, :rel => 'external nofollow' %>, <%= link_to 'musician', music_url %>, <%= link_to 'wanna be designer', dribbble_url, :rel => 'external nofollow' %>, and burger connoisseur. I live in San Francisco. I previously worked at <a href="http://heysynthetic.com" rel="external nofollow">Synthetic</a> (the makers of <a href="http://hipstamatic.com" rel="external nofollow">Hipstamatic</a>).</p>

  <p>Now, I'm the VP of Engineering at <a href="https://seesaw.co" rel="external nofollow">Seesaw</a>. I also work on <a href="https://cheddarapp.com" rel="external nofollow">Cheddar</a> in my spare time</em>. Checkout my <%= link_to 'recent projects', projects_url %>.</p>

  <p>I <%= link_to 'make music', music_url %> sometimes. I'm also in a band called <a href="http://findingchesterfield.com" rel="external nofollow">Finding Chesterfield</a>. I am always in constant pursuit of tasting the perfect burger.</p>

  <p>When the iPhone SDK first came out in 2008, I wrote this app called <a href="http://www.youversion.com/mobile" rel="external nofollow">Bible</a> that launched day one of the App Store. There are millions of people using it now, which is really humbling. I used to own a few companies, freelanced, and worked at some startups. Ask me about it <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?screen_name=soffes">on Twitter</a> if you're curious.</p>

  <p>The best way to get to know me is to listen to <a href="http://5by5.tv/founderstalk/38" rel="external nofollow">part 1</a> and <a href="http://5by5.tv/founderstalk/38" rel="external nofollow">part 2</a> of the Founders Talk about my life, <a href="http://nothingmagical.com" rel="external nofollow">Nothing Magical</a>, and making <a href="http://cheddarapp.com" rel="external nofollow">Cheddar</a>.</p>

  <p>You can <%= link_to 'download my résumé', resume_url %> if you want. <em>I'm not looking for a full time job, but you can <a href="http://hire.samsoff.es/" rel="external nofollow">hire me</a> for limited work</em>. <%= mail_to 'sam@soff.es', 'Email me', :encode => 'hex' %> and say hi if you're feeling friendly.</p>
  <p style="text-align:center;margin:2em 0 -1em"><%= follow_button(size: 'large') %></p>
</section>
